post_text:
DAY CAMP AT HOME
The Voyageur’s Area Council of the Boy Scouts of America is offering an activity that all youth and families can enjoy from home on their own time called “Summer Camp in a Box” that you can order on their website. It will have craft projects, a scavenger hunt, games and activities related to “Down on the Farm” their theme for camp this summer. The cost is $25 to have it mailed right to your house per unit. They will take orders for the units until noon on Wednesday, June 24th and then will put these units together and send them out.

Sign up at: http://www.vac-bsa.org/Event.aspx?id=9067

GEARING UP FOR GROWING SEASON - Two Harbors Class
Do you have an interest in gardening and are looking for ideas and tips to get your growing season off to a good start? Learn why gardening is important, the different types of gardens, and how to have success in our short growing season. We will explore ways to extend our short growing season as well as discuss plant varieties that do well in our growing zone. For beginners through experienced gardeners. Register by 3/16.

FEELING FIT - Two Harbors Class
Join us for a fun, new class that will work every muscle in your body! Feeling Fit will incorporate circuit training and interval training through the use of stations. We will use weights, exercises sliders, exercise bands, fitness balls and dynamic resistance. We will also borrow elements from Yoga and Pilates to work our core and improve our balance. Each class will end with stretching, relaxation and a new recipe to try! What to bring: tennis shoes, water bottle, weights if you prefer to use your own. No class 3/23, 4/6, 5/25. Register by 2/26.
Instructor: Jillian McCorison
Minnehaha Gym
Mondays, 6-7 p.m.
March 2 - June 1
Class fee: $83
Register online at https://isd381.cr3.rschooltoday.com/public/getcategory/program_id/6 OR call 218-834-8201, ext. 8230.

post_text:
PUPPY PRESCHOOL - Two Harbors Class
For puppies 10 - 18 weeks old. Puppy chewing, nipping, and jumping on you? Learn tips and skills to survive puppyhood as you teach good behavior like sitting, leash manners, and coming when called. You’ll also play confidence building games with puppy, using various everyday items. Puppies attending classes designed to meet their unique physical and mental needs grow up to become great dogs! Prerequisites: Bring to first class proof of first set of vaccines and deworming (given at least 7 days prior)

Supplies student needs to bring: Flat buckle collar or harness (no choke or pinch/prong), 4-6 foot leash (no retractable leashes), lots of small, soft, yummy treats (chicken, hotdogs, cheese, dog treats), poop bags. Supplies available at many retailers; costs vary. No class 2/19. FIRST CLASS AT 6:45-8:00 PM. Register by 2/5.
Register online at https://isd381.cr3.rschooltoday.com/public/getcategory/program_id/6 or call 218-834-8201, ext. 8230.

ABDUCTION RESISTANCE (Two Harbors Class)
Students will learn self-protection in age appropriate terms related to stranger abduction: Role playing of safety scenarios; Proper use of progressive resistance when contacted, confronted, or attacked; Basic escapes, striking, and kicking techniques as self-defense against abduction. Class will involve physical practice combined with lecture and video lessons. Parents are welcome. Instructor is a certified black belt karate instructor through the World Tang Soo Do Association. No charge for this class - but YOU MUST REGISTER.
Instructor: Rick Peterson
Minnehaha Gym
Tuesday & Thursday, November 12 & 14
3:45 - 5:15 PM
Register online or call 218-834-8201, ext. 8230.

post_text:
BE THE HELP!!! ~ Silver Bay Class

Emergencies happen every day – accidents, fires, floods, heart attacks, etc. 95% of first help during emergencies comes from family, friends and neighbors like you. Learn to stay safe, stop the bleed, provide support, and get help. Practice first aid & triage, using fire extinguishers, and basic search & rescue in a casual atmosphere. Build your own evacuation and shelter kits. This Community Emergency Response Training (CERT) weekend class is for ages 15 and up (<18 with adult permission). If interested, students can then apply to join the Lake County CERT team. No experience needed. Please wear casual clothing for working on the floor, work gloves and a notebook.
Fri. 1pm - 8pm
Sat. 9am - 5pm
Sun. 9am - 4pm
Mary Mac Center, Room 22
$10.00
https://isd381.cr3.rschooltoday.com/public/costoption/class_id/4829/public/1/sp/

Calling all Little Agates and Little Mariners!

To assure your slot in our Silver Bay and Two Harbors Community Education PreSchool sections, registration must take place as soon as possible. Our classes are Parent Aware 4 Star rated. Minnesota Early Learning Scholarships as well as district tuition support are available via application. Some transportation options can also be arranged.

PreK 3. Must be age 3 on or before September 1, 2019 and be toilet trained. Our 3's attend 2 days a week for 2 1/2 hours each day for a total of 5 hours a week.

PreK 4 Must be age 4 on or before Sept. 1, 2019. Our 4's attend 12 hours a week.

PreK 3/4 (Two Harbors only.) Same age requirements as above. This class is 16 hours a week (mornings M-TH)

Call 834-8201, ext 8230 or 218-4437 ext 8137 for additional information by June 6th. Online Registration: https://isd381.cr3.rschooltoday.com/public/home/.

post_text:
Edible Gardening - Silver Bay

Are you interested in growing your own food but you are limited by space, know how, or time? This course will help you to decide what, where and how to grow some of our favorite fruits and vegetables. Despite our limited growing season, there are many edibles that do well in our climate, and many are able to be grown in containers. We'll discuss the best varieties for some of these limiting situations, proper growing requirements and long term care for several vegetables, herbs and fruits.

5/1/2019
5:30-7:00pm in WKS Room 115
$8.00

Are you interested in learning more about providing child care in your home? This is a great opportunity!
Child Care Licensing 101: In Home Family Child Care Anyone interested in exploring the basics of starting a child care business in their home.
Parents who use child care entrust their children to a care provider for many hours each day. Licensing child care providers helps protect the health and safety of children by requiring that certain minimum standards of care are met.
This session will provide a basic overview of licensing rules and regulations, qualifications of the provider and the provider’s home and how to begin the licensing process. There is no charge for this class but you must register.
Instructor: Theresa Reineccius, Licensor (Lake County Health & Human Services)

Two Harbors, April 23 at 5:30 PM in the THHS Community Room.

Input asked - IRRRB

Take this opportunity to express your opinion regarding the IRRR - Iron Range Resources & Rehabilitation

Stakeholder Survey
From Deputy Commissioner Jason Metsa and Commissioner Mark Phillips

You are invited to help the Department of Iron Range Resources & Rehabilitation develop its next strategic plan. We will use your comments and suggestions to help ensure that we create a roadmap for the future reflects the priorities of the public we serve.

The agency will use the strategic plan to help realize its vision for the region: Advancing regional growth by stabilizing and enhancing the economy of northeastern Minnesota.

Iron Range Resources & Rehabilitation's mission - the way it goes about realizing its vision - is to promote and invest in business, community and workforce development for the betterment of northeastern Minnesota

We look forward to your responses to the questions that follow.

The survey takes less than five minutes to complete.

Survey deadline: Thursday, March 14

Lake County Emergency Alerts - New system

Get emergency and urgent notices by signing up for "Lake County Emergency Alerts." This allows the county to reach you quickly with critical information like evacuations, shelter-in-place warnings, road closures, law enforcement safety messages, etc.

You can receive these messages for multiple locations (home, work, cabin, childcare, etc) and by whatever methods you choose (voice, emails and text). For text messages, please add 893-61 to your caller ID to identify these alerts.

If you were previously registered for emergency notifications through CodeRED, you need to re-register for Lake County Emergency Alerts. Lake County will no longer use CodeRED after February 28, 2019.

Lake County respects your privacy. Your personal information will not be shared, except as required by law, and will only be used to send urgent messages from Lake County Sheriff or Emergency Management.

Dog Obedience Training -

The purpose of this course is to prepare you and to teach your dog good citizenship--heel, sit, stay, down, come, and stand. This is not an entry level puppy class. post_text:
SILVER BAY CLASS:
Tuesday Morning SomaYoga Flow Yoga

A blend of a blend of hatha yoga: (mind awareness, body alignment, breath practices and meditation) and somatics (which works with voluntary muscles and brain reeducation.) Class concentrates on breath awareness and breath practices, uses Mudras and Mantras, asana , relaxation, and meditation to dive into all layers of mind, body and soul. Students flow from one posture into the next, focusing on their energy flow through the body and their breath letting this be their teacher. Water bottle recommended.
FOCUS: Increase flexibility, strength & stability
This class incorporates breath work and postures to increase the body’s alignment, strength and flexibility. Emphasis on the inner core, building awareness, and finding ease in the body. 7 sessions.
$84.00

Silver Bay - Lifeguarding Class (American Red Cross):

HAVING FUN WITH PASTA
Have you have ever wanted to try to make your own pasta but were not ready to try it alone? If yes, then this is the class for you. Pasta is all about taste and texture and is one of the easiest and most versatile foods to prepare. In this class, you will be taught the basics of pasta making. The ingredients and recipe will be supplied. All you will need to bring is a rolling pin, apron, container to bring your pasta home, and a desire to have fun! Register by 1/15.
Instructor: Barb Mason
THHS FACS Room 2305
Tuesday, 6:00 - 9:00 PM
Class Fee: $26
Register online or call 218-834-8201, ext. 8230.

Driver Improvement 4-Hour Refresher
This driver improvement refresher course is for anyone who has already taken the 8 hour, first time class. Completion of this class qualifies for a 10% reduction on automobile insurance premiums in MN for those ages 55 and over. Please bring a pen or pencil. Feel free to bring a drink and snack to enjoy during the class.

post_text:
DOG OBEDIENCE CLASS
The purpose of this course is to prepare you and to teach your dog good citizenship--heel, sit, stay, down, come, and stand. This is not an entry level puppy class. At the first class you must provide veterinary records as proof that DHLPP and Rabies vaccinations are up to date - No Exceptions! Your signature is required on the liability waiver at registration. Bring a leash and pinch collar. Retractable leashes are discouraged; standard leashes 6 feet or shorter are recommended. Owners WILL be responsible to clean up after their dog. DO NOT BRING YOUR DOG TO THE FIRST CLASS. Register by 1/10 .
Instructor: Chad Hamman
THHS Jr. High Wing, Lower Hall
Wednesdays, Jan. 16 - Feb. 27, 6:00 - 7:00 PM
Class fee: $75
Register online or in the Community Ed. Office.

If you have a talent, skill, or passion for something that could be taught in an evening Community Ed. class, please consider teaching a class this winter or spring.

The class can be just one evening or several evenings; you set the time and length of class. You can also choose how much you would like to be paid for teaching the class (within reason of course).

The winter quarter runs from January 14th to February 28th and we need the class information no later than Monday, November 19.

Please share your talents with our communities!

Thank you!!

jhipple@isd381.org Silver Bay

post_text:
NATIVE BEES AND THEIR IMPORTANCE IN YOUR LANDSCAPE.
Are you interested in growing healthier happier plants in your landscape? Did you know that there are over 400 species of native bees in Minnesota, and they are essential in the health of many of our native plants, shrubs and trees? They also fill a large role in pollinating many of our vegetables, ornamental flowers, and herbs. Even better still, many of our native bees are stingless, meaning they are safe to encourage living on your property. If you are interested in better understanding native bees, how to support them within your own property, and what they can do for you, join us for a session all about bees. Register by 10/15.

post_text:
Not just for Drivers Ed Students!

If you're renewing a driver license in MN, this is now optional before you go to take less time in the DMV. DE instructor Chris Belanger just did it, and said it was pretty painless.

With the launch of the new FAST/DS system on October 1, take a moment to learn about the importance of the new pre-application feature. This process will allow applicants to enter a significant portion of their driver’s license application online before going into a driver’s license office. This process takes about 10-15 minutes and will cut down on wait times at the driver’s license office. Consider completing the pre-application. This feature can also be used by anyone who is renewing their MN license or requesting a duplicate MN license, in addition to anyone who is obtaining a MN credential for the first time.

Pre-application can be found on our website at: (https://dps.mn.gov/divisions/dvs/Pages/default.aspx)

Click on the box on the right side that states “PRE-APPLY for a Driver’s License or ID.” and follow the directions.

vol·un·teer.
[ˌvälənˈtir]
NOUN
.
1.a person who freely offers to take part in an enterprise or undertake a task.

We're looking for additional residents to serve on the Lake Superior School District Community Education Advisory Council. This council is responsible for public input on our
after school programs, adult education, youth activities, community use of school facilities, early childhood family education, preschool and more. The council meets four times a year. If you are interested or would like more information, please contact Chris Langenbrunner, Community Education Director at 218-834-8201, ext. 8227. clangenbrunner@isd381.org
